The paper proposes an auxiliary module to improve the performance of Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) in molecular graph analysis. GNNs are a popular architecture for analyzing chemical molecules, which falls under the domain of material and medicinal science. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
